SUMMARY:Practicing Law as a Christian
DESCRIPTION:Naomi Y. Kwang (IU McKinney School of Law '14)\, is a Partner
  at Barnes &amp\; Thornburg in Indianapolis and currently serves as Chair
  for their greater China and South East Asia corporate division. She has 
 spent her career practicing corporate law\, M&amp\;A\, and international 
 business law. She will be speaking about her journey as a Christian attor
 ney\, how her relationship with Jesus has guided her\, and how to practic
 e law as a Christian.&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Naomi Y. Kwang (IU McKinney School of L
 aw '14)\, is a Partner at Barnes &amp\; Thornburg in Indianapolis and cur
 rently serves as Chair for their greater China and South East Asia corpor
 ate division. She has spent her career practicing corporate law\, M&amp\;
 A\, and international business law. She will be speaking about her journe
 y as a Christian attorney\, how her relationship with Jesus has guided he
 r\, and how to practice law as a Christian.&#160\;</p>
