SUMMARY:Neuro-Hacks: How the Most Productive Attorneys are Rewiring Their
  Brains for Long Term Resilience and Thriving
DESCRIPTION:Join Ashley Hart\, Executive Director of JLAP\, as she discus
 ses why attorneys face disproportionately high rates of mental health and
  substance abuse challenges\; common misconceptions about what mental hea
 lth and substance abuse crises look like\, and how to recognize early war
 ning signs\; neuroplasticity and the brain's capacity to adapt\, recover\
 , and build resilience\; Practical tools and habits that successful attor
 neys use to sustainably manage the demands of the profession.&#160\;  RSV
 P on CareerNet. Food will be provided for those who RSVP by noon the day 
 before the event.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Join Ashley Hart\, Executive Director o
 f JLAP\, as she discusses why attorneys face disproportionately high rate
 s of mental health and substance abuse challenges\; common misconceptions
  about what mental health and substance abuse crises look like\, and how 
 to recognize early warning signs\; neuroplasticity and the brain's capaci
 ty to adapt\, recover\, and build resilience\; Practical tools and habits
  that successful attorneys use to sustainably manage the demands of the p
 rofession.&#160\;</p><p>  RSVP on CareerNet. Food will be provided for th
 ose who RSVP by noon the day before the event.</p>
UID:20260416T160000Z-2249711@events.iu.edu
DTSTAMP:20260326T081620Z
