SUMMARY:Prepare to Practice Workshop Series: Regulatory Research and Indi
 ana-Specific Resources
DESCRIPTION:Join Morgan Kelly\, Student Engagement Librarian\, for an ove
 rview of regulatory research and Indiana-specific resources! Learn about 
 the basics of conducting research on administrative regulations and explo
 re the best resources for Indiana state law.__________________________Loo
 king forward to the end of exams and the start of your summer employment?
  Consider attending the Jerome Hall Law Library's "Prepare to Practice" w
 orkshop sessions!Each year\, the Jerome Hall Law Library offers a series 
 of workshops and information sessions to help students prepare for their 
 summer positions. These sessions offer Maurer students an opportunity to 
 review\, refresh\, and refine their legal research techniques as they pre
 pare for their summer roles. Each workshop focuses on reinforcing foundat
 ional skills\, exploring effective research approaches\, and helping stud
 ents feel more confident in tackling real-world research tasks.If you hav
 e any questions\, please contact Morgan Kelly\, Student Engagement Librar
 ian\, via email atkellyms@iu.edu.
