X-SOURCE:IU Maurer School of Law
DTSTART:20260508T230000Z
DTEND:20260509T020000Z
LOCATION:Jerome Hall Law Library - Room Number: Lobby &amp\; Reading Room
SUMMARY:Class of 2026 Graduation Party
DESCRIPTION:Join your classmates for an evening of celebration at the Cla
 ss of 2026 Graduation Party\, hosted by the Jerome Hall Law Library. Enjo
 y refreshments\, a selfie station\, live music\, and a formal recognition
  programâ€”all while taking in the beautiful view of Dunn's Woods from th
 e Library's Reading Room.  Doors open at 7 pm. The program will begin at 
 approximately 8:00 pm\, during which law school faculty and staff will re
 cognize various graduating students for academic\, advocacy\, clinical\, 
 and pro bono accomplishments as well as announce the winners of several a
 wards voted on by the Class of 2026.Each registered guest will receive on
 e drink ticket. IDs are required when presenting the ticket to the barten
 der.  Due to strict capacity guidelines\, attendance is limited to gradua
 tes\, their guests\, and law school faculty and staff. Each graduate may 
 bring up to two guests. RSVPs are required by Wednesday\, April 29.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Join your classmates for an evening of 
 celebration at the Class of 2026 Graduation Party\, hosted by the Jerome 
 Hall Law Library. Enjoy refreshments\, a selfie station\, live music\, an
 d a formal recognition programâ€”all while taking in the beautiful view o
 f Dunn's Woods from the Library's Reading Room.</p><p>  Doors open at 7 p
 m. The program will begin at approximately 8:00 pm\, during which law sch
 ool faculty and staff will recognize various graduating students for acad
 emic\, advocacy\, clinical\, and pro bono accomplishments as well as anno
 unce the winners of several awards voted on by the Class of 2026.</p><p><
 strong>Each registered guest will receive one drink ticket. IDs are requi
 red when presenting the ticket to the bartender.</strong></p><p>  Due to 
 strict capacity guidelines\, attendance is limited to graduates\, their g
 uests\, and law school faculty and staff. Each graduate may bring up to t
 wo guests. <strong>RSVPs are required by Wednesday\, April 29.</strong></
 p>
